==Media releases==
[[Acorn Media UK]] announced it would release series two on [[DVD]] and [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]] in the United Kingdom on 23 March 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acorndvd.com/broadchurch-s2-bluray.html|title=Broadchurch, Series Two (BluRay)|website=Acorn Media UK|date=December 2014|accessdate=4 January 2015}}; {{cite web|url=http://www.acorndvd.com/broadchurch-s2.html|title=Broadchurch, Series Two|website=Acorn Media UK|date=December 2014|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref>

==Cast==
[[File:2009 07 31 David Tennant smile 08 (cropped to shoulders).jpg|thumb|David Tennant.]]
[[File:Jodie Whittaker cropped.jpg|thumb|Jodie Whittaker.]]
Characters in series two of ''Broadchurch'' included the following:

===The police===
* Detective Inspector Alec Hardy ([[David Tennant]]) <U+2013> invalided off the Broadchurch police force at the end of series one due to poor health, Hardy struggles with severe heart disease while continuing to assist the prosecution in its case against Joe Miller.
* Detective Sergeant Ellie Miller ([[Olivia Colman]]) <U+2013> a local detective married to Joe Miller, and mother to 12-year-old Tom and three-year-old Fred. She berates herself for not recognizing the problems that led her husband to have a relationship with the dead boy, and suffers from guilt issues.
* SOCO Brian Young ([[Peter de Jersey]]) <U+2013> a [[Scenes of Crime Officer]] with the Broadchurch police force.
<!-- DO NOT INCLUDE until confirmed by airing * Chief Superintendent Elaine Jenkinson ([[Tracey Childs]]) - head of the Broadchurch police. -->

===The Latimers===
* Beth Latimer ([[Jodie Whittaker]]) <U+2013> mother to Chloe and murder victim Danny, and Mark's wife. She still struggles with grief issues, and is increasingly bitter and angry toward her former friend, Ellie Miller. Beth's pregnancy, which began in series one, comes to term.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/broadchurch-returns-what-we-know-so-far-ahead-of-tonights-first-episode-9957594.html|last=Denham|first=Jess|title=Broadchurch series 2: What we know so far ahead of tonight's first episode|newspaper=The Independent|date=5 January 2015|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref>
* Mark Latimer ([[Andrew Buchan]]) <U+2013> father to Chloe and murder victim Danny, and Beth's husband. His son's death helped him to reconcile with his wife after he had an affair with local hotelkeeper Becca Fisher, but the problems in his marriage didn't go away.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/broadchurch-series-2-jodie-whittaker-says-new-series-will-not-be-like-midsomer-murders-9958768.html|last=Debnath|first=Neela|title=Broadchurch series 2: Jodie Whittaker says new series will not be like Midsomer Murders|newspaper=The Independent|date=5 January 2015|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref>
* Chloe Latimer (Charlotte Beaumont) <U+2013> Beth and Mark's 16-year old daughter.
* Liz Roper ([[Susan Brown (actress)|Susan Brown]]) <U+2013> Beth's mother, she is a devoutly religious woman.

===The Millers===
* Lucy Stevens ([[Tanya Franks]]) <U+2013> sister of DS Ellie Miller and mother of Oliver "Olly" Stevens, she has a gambling habit.
* Tom Miller (Adam Wilson) <U+2013> Ellie and Joe's 12-year-old elder son.
<!--* Joe Miller ([[Matthew Gravelle]]) <U+2013> Ellie's husband and father to 12-year-old Tom and three-year-old Fred. Joe murdered Danny Latimer in series one,<!--Per [[WP:SPOILER]], this content should not be removed. Wikipedia is not censored.-- > and is now on trial.-->

===Members of the press===
* Maggie Radcliffe ([[Carolyn Pickles]]) <U+2013> editor of the local newspaper, the ''Broadchurch Echo''.
* Oliver "Olly" Stevens ([[Jonathan Bailey (actor)|Jonathan Bailey]]) <U+2013> Lucy Stevens' son and Ellie Miller's nephew, he is a reporter for the ''Broadchurch Echo''.

===The townspeople===
* Sharon Bishop ([[Marianne Jean-Baptiste]])<ref name=twonames>{{cite news|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-12-19/new-pictures-from-broadchurch-series-two-but-whats-with-all-the-bluebells|last=Lazarus|first=Susanna|title=New pictures from Broadchurch series two <U+2013> but what's with all the bluebells?|newspaper=Radio Times|date=19 December 2014|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref> <U+2013> 
* Nigel "Nige" Carter ([[Joe Sims (actor)|Joe Sims]]) <U+2013> Mark Latimer's best friend and co-worker at the plumbing company. His secret late-night trips with Danny were not known by the Latimers until some months after the boy's death, and this causes tension between him and Mark.
* Reverend Paul Coates ([[Arthur Darvill]]) <U+2013> a young Anglican priest in Broadchurch.
* Becca Fisher ([[Simone McAullay]]) <U+2013> the owner and manager of the Trader Hotel who once had an affair with Mark Latimer.
* Jocelyn Knight ([[Charlotte Rampling]]) <U+2013> a Broadchurch resident, Danny Latimer argued with the postman near her home a short time before he was murdered. The character's name is an [[in-joke]] on the series.<ref name=ramplingexotic>{{cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/film/2014/dec/20/-sp-charlotte-rampling-im-exotic-and-i-like-that|last=Elmhirst|first=Sophie|title=Charlotte Rampling: 'I'm exotic, and I like that'|newspaper=The Guardian|date=20 December 2014|accessdate=20 December 2014}}</ref>
* Claire Ripley ([[Eve Myles]])<ref name=twonames /> <U+2013> 
* Sonia Sharma ([[Meera Syal]])<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/episode/ddg8yr/broadchurch--series-2---episode-2|title=Broadchurch: Series 2 - Episode 2|newspaper=Radio Times|date=31 December 2014|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref> <U+2013> 
* Abby Thompson ([[Phoebe Waller-Bridge]])<ref name=twonames /> <U+2013> 
* Susan Wright ([[Pauline Quirke]]) <U+2013> Nigel's biological mother, whose first husband raped and then murdered their daughter. Embittered by her incarceration as an accessory (she denied her guilt), she sought to reconcile with Nigel, whom authorities took from her and placed for adoption. She fled Broadchurch as the search for Danny's killer reached its climax, but is a critical eyewitness to the crime.
* Lee ([[James D'Arcy]])<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/episode/dc7w9d/broadchurch--series-2---episode-1|title=Broadchurch: Series 2 - Episode 1|newspaper=Radio Times|date=31 December 2014|accessdate=4 January 2015}}</ref> <U+2013> 
<!-- DO NOT INCLUDE until confirmed by airing * Dean Thomas ([[Jacob Anderson]]) - a 17-year-old local man, he is the boyfriend of Chloe Latimer. His drug dealing was covered up by Chloe in series one. -->
{{clear}}

